<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You want it? You got it punk!</span><hr size=1> I have had precisely enough of this 1 to 10PP undercutting of high-end brewed beverages. There are damn few things we Grandmaster Brewers can make and sell at a hefty profit. You wanna mess with me? You got me. I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>guarantee</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that I can make <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> anything</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> you can make, and succeed more often, thus making my cost less. I will drop the cost on what I'm making to coppers above cost, and everyone will buy from me, and you, you ignorant little Johnny-come-lately, will have no customer base whatsoever.<br>
<br>
As has been argued eloquently and often both here and on the boards over at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/beqtraderscorner">EQTraders</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, it is in <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>everyone's</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> best interest to match the lowest price. Don't go under it, don't play the &quot;I'll sell for less than you&quot; game. You'll piss me off enough to play the same game, and in the end, you will lose. Badly. Undercut me by 10? I'll come back and undercut you by 50. I have already made the investment to Grandmaster my skill (ok, so I have one more stinkin' point to go; that'll be done soon enough), so I don't need to sell this stuff for a profit to pay for increasing my skill; I will happily sell this stuff at cost to provide a service to the community and to make you poor. If I get angry enough, I might even sell at a loss. Try me. I don't want to be a Lorec or a Bend and ruin the market for everyone, but if you're gonna keep it up, I'll go straight to the bottom and crash the market. If I have to spend every in-game moment for the next month doing nothing but brewing to make it happen, I will.<br>
<br>
