That's just deflation.  Assuming drop rates remain constant, the price on all items goes down over time.  Handwraps sold for about 6K or so when they first hit the FV marketplace, nowadays they go for about 2K.  The same is true of crafted goods.  As time wears on, the demand for banded just isn't as high as it was when the server first opened, so it sells for less.<br>
<br>
I mentioned blue diamonds as just an example of how, with dropped items, you can't really ruin the economy by undercutting everyone else because the limited supply prevents you from doing it.  No one can go out and farm up enough blue diamonds to satisfy the demand if they start selling them dirt cheap.  If I started selling blue diamonds for 500 plat to undercut someone, they'd probably just buy them all from me and sell them to others for 1500 again.<br>
